1970_United_States_census" title="1970 United States census">1970</a></th><td>241,420</td><td></td><td>19.8%</td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><a href="/wiki/1980_United_States_census" title="1980 United States census">1980</a></th><td>315,474</td><td></td><td>30.7%</td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><a href="/wiki/1990_United_States_census" title="1990 United States census">1990</a></th><td>395,934</td><td></td><td>25.5%</td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><a href="/wiki/2000_United_States_census" title="2000 United States census">2000</a></th><td>540,828</td><td></td><td>36.6%</td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><a href="/wiki/2010_United_States_census" title="2010 United States census">2010</a></th><td>731,424</td><td></td><td>35.2%</td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><a href="/wiki/2020_United_States_census" title="2020 United States census">2020</a></th><td>874,579</td><td></td><td>19.6%</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">2024 (est.)</th><td class="us-census-pop-estimate">943,475</td><td><sup id="cite&#95;ref-QuickFacts&#95;11-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-QuickFacts-11"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>10<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></td><td>7.9%</td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" class="us-census-pop-footnote" style="text-align: center">U.S. Decennial Census<sup id="cite&#95;ref-DecennialCensus&#95;144-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-DecennialCensus-144"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>140<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><br />1800–1900<sup id="cite&#95;ref-histnc&#95;145-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-histnc-145"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>141<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> 2010–2020<sup id="cite&#95;ref-QuickFacts&#95;11-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-QuickFacts-11"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>10<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></td></tr>
